~ Vincent_Dialogue
Sign: Sup gang this sign was left by Vincent the anti Capitalism miner (died before autonomous miners). We run this place, every village around this parts (butterfly grove) tries to craft their own autonomous guardian these days, but we're irreplaceable, right? Ore sells better than ever before, they need it for those miner ground born freaks so we run the economy.
Sign: Here's how you use that drill thing in yo hands: hands on the mouse and HOLD LEFT CLICK to mine tiles creative input mapping right?
Sign: I'd tell you how to move but you probably figured it if u reached this sign I guess, you can move on multiple layers when your current layer gets boring or if you don't feel like mining what's ahead of you. I bet ya didn't know that, hold CTRL to see the previous (green) and next (red) layers you can move on ?5 layers?, or how many the devs decided are enough. Then press Q (backwards) and E (Forward) to switch between them, cool ass mechanic.
Sign: If you're actually reading this, know that inflation is a bitch, if you want to know more about it search: "disclaimer, we were forced to remove this joke", vary the resources you sell, or they're gonna generate market pressure, market pressure leads to inflation because prices increase fast in this small community, and when one village gets a lot of something you bet they're gonna sky rocket the price for "that thang", so try to sell variety, when you can't dig deeper upgrade your drill. Good luck miner!
=> END